# ATV-bench Community League — code ownership / mandatory review (santa round-8).
#
# GitHub runs a `pull_request` workflow from the PR's OWN copy of the workflow file, so a
# malicious submission PR could rewrite the pr-path-guard / league scorer to no-op itself.
# The platform's answer to that is NOT more workflow code (the PR can rewrite it too) — it
# is REQUIRED CODE-OWNER REVIEW on the sensitive paths, enforced by branch protection
# ("Require review from Code Owners" + "Include administrators"). A PR that edits any path
# below cannot merge without an explicit maintainer approval, which is exactly the manual
# inspection GitHub's fork-PR security model depends on.
#
# Community submission PRs (touching only league/submissions/<author>/{main.py,
# submission.json}) match NONE of these patterns, so they need no code-owner review and the
# always-on ci.yml pr-path-guard confines them. Any PR that also touches the trust-critical
# surfaces below is forced through a maintainer.

# The workflows themselves — the scorer, the publisher, the deploy, and the always-on gate.
/.github/                       @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers

# The durable store the leaderboard is rebuilt from — never a community submission's to edit.
/league/matches.jsonl           @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers

# The trusted publish/scoring code and its guards.
/src/                           @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers
/pyproject.toml                 @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers
/leaderboard/schema.json        @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers

# Local evaluators, their executable image inputs, and the tests that enforce the
# Actions-never-evaluate invariant are trust-critical even though Actions do not run them.
/arena/                         @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers
/tests/                         @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers
/uv.lock                        @All-The-Vibes/league-maintainers
